urt Physician Between <italic>Aufkl&#x000e4;rung</italic> und <italic>Reaktion?</italic>,&#x0201d; in <italic>Medicine in Enlightenment Europe,</italic> eds. Ole Peter Grell and Andrew Cunningham (to be published by Ashgate in 2007); and with Roger Cooter, &#x0201c;Thinking in Pictures&#x02014;AIDS and the Problem of Public Health Posters&#x0201d; (Special Issue of <italic>Medizinhistorisches Journal</italic>, forthcoming 2007).</p></bio></contrib></contrib-group><pub-date pub-type="ppub"><season>Winter</season><year>2006</year></pub-date><volume>80</volume><issue>4</issue><fpage>617</fpage><lpage>648</lpage><copyright-statement>Copyright &#x000a9; 2006 The Johns Hopkins University Press</copyright-statement><copyright-year>2006</copyright-year><license license-type="open-access" xlink:href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/"><p>This 
